    </script><script data-n-head="ssr" src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id=GTM-5NWTPH" crossorigin="anonymous" async></script><script data-n-head="ssr" src="https://cdn.klook.com/s/dist_web/common/galileo/1.10.0/galileo.umd.js" type="text/javascript"></script><script data-n-head="ssr" type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"name":"Home","@id":"https://www.klook.com/en-US/"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"name":"Italy","@id":"https://www.klook.com/en-US/destination/co1027-italy/"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"name":"Rome"}}]}</script><script data-n-head="ssr" type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the rainiest month in Rome?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"November is the rainiest month in Rome, with about 4–5 inches of rainfall. It’s a good time to visit indoor sites like the Vatican Museums or Capitoline Museums while enjoying the cozy side of the Eternal City.\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Rome walkable?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! Many tourist attractions in Rome are within walking distance, like the Piazza Navona, Trevi Fountain, and Campo de Fiori. Wear comfy shoes for the cobblestone streets and enjoy the lively squares along the way.\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Rome very expensive?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Rome can be pricey, but you can manage costs by eating at local trattorias and using public transport. Budget travelers spend around €55–€120 daily, while luxury stays in this Italian city can cost much more during high season.\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Rome in Italy known for?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Rome is known for its ancient history, Roman monuments, and iconic landmarks like the Colosseum, Trevi Fountain, and Vatican City. The city is also famous for its amazing Italian food like pasta and amazing fountains and churches from Roman times.\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the best month to travel to Rome?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The best time to visit Rome, Italy, is April, May, September, or October. These months offer pleasant weather and fewer tourists at popular attractions in Rome, Italy, like the Colosseum and Roman Forum.\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Where to stay in Rome?\n","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For your first visit, stay in the Historic Center (Centro Storico) for easy access to top Rome landmarks. Trastevere offers a charming neighborhood feel, while Piazza di Spagna and Prati are great for style and safety near Vatican City. Budget travelers can stay near Termini Station, though it’s busier at night.\n"}}]}</script> <!-- title-->

