ead more","tag":[{"bg_color":"","text_color":"","text":"Transport"}]},"track_info":{"object_id":"blog_rome-public-transportation","extra":{"LinkURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fblog\u002Frome-public-transportation\u002F","GeneralTagList":"Transport"}}}]}}}},{"meta":{"type":"any","placeholder":"","track":{"iht_spm":"Review_LIST","iht_extra_info":null},"name":"DestinationReview"},"data":null,"body":{"content":{"handler":"marketing","data_type":"DestinationReview","load_type":"sync","src":"","track":null,"data":{"title":"Reviews of Rome activities","review_list":{"aggregate_id":"92","review_list":[{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F18001-tuscany-tour-lunch-wine-rome\u002F","id":18001,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fncmgcq1cco1f0rtxednf.jpg","name":"12-Hour Tuscany with 3-Course Lunch and Wine Tasting Tour"},"review_content":"The tour was amazing. Guide give us a lot of information about the area. Wine tasting was good even tho I dont usually drink it.","review_id":18420037,"translate_content":"The tour was amazing. Guide give us a lot of information about the area. Wine tasting was good even tho I dont usually drink it.","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-05-10 02:52:37","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Klook User","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F103080-trastevere-food-tour-rome\u002F","id":103080,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fjhrclnfntdwfsc6strgl.jpg","name":"Trastevere Food Tour in Rome"},"review_content":"Overall, a good experience. We enjoyed a wide variety of tastings, including two types of cheese (such as Parmigiana), wine, prosciutto, supplì, three types of roman pizza slices, and a seated pasta course with wine, finishing with gelato.\nOur guide, Karina, was friendly and shared interesting insights about the history of the food, as well as Roman culture and traditions. It would be even better if more details about the neighbourhood and key highlights of Trastevere could be included during the walk.","review_id":17765259,"translate_content":"Overall, a good experience. We enjoyed a wide variety of tastings, including two types of cheese (such as Parmigiana), wine, prosciutto, supplì, three types of roman pizza slices, and a seated pasta course with wine, finishing with gelato.\nOur guide, Karina, was friendly and shared interesting insights about the history of the food, as well as Roman culture and traditions. It would be even better if more details about the neighbourhood and key highlights of Trastevere could be included during the walk.","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-02-16 22:51:23","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Nima **********","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F173934-rome-underground-cave-tasting-of-lazio-wines-and-cheeses\u002F","id":173934,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fgp06odrispnewlv3ivk5.jpg","name":"Rome: Wine & Food Tasting in Europe’s First Urban Cheese Aging Cave"},"review_content":"An amazing experience with Antonio and Alessia! Very informative and tasty, delicious cheese, fantastic wine, and a great atmosphere. Definitely recommend when visiting Rome!","review_id":18618336,"translate_content":"An amazing experience with Antonio and Alessia! Very informative and tasty, delicious cheese, fantastic wine, and a great atmosphere. Definitely recommend when visiting Rome!","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-05-29 07:56:52","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Klook User","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F135370-hard-rock-cafe-dining-experience-in-rome\u002F","id":135370,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Ft4jwirjmoatvxtr30qma.jpg","name":"Hard Rock Cafe Dining Experience in Rome"},"review_content":"amazing! we thought there might be extra charges like table or service charge.. but it’s really NO hidden cost. we bought the gold menu, showed the QR , ate and left! The service was also top notch! the two servers I think her name was manalisa or Marissa as well as “ulin or wulin” from Indonesia. they are brilliant and so warm and friendly ","review_id":18181964,"translate_content":"amazing! we thought there might be extra charges like table or service charge.. but it’s really NO hidden cost. we bought the gold menu, showed the QR , ate and left! The service was also top notch! the two servers I think her name was manalisa or Marissa as well as “ulin or wulin” from Indonesia. they are brilliant and so warm and friendly ","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-04-02 21:22:00","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Jo *******","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F141993-pasta-ravioli-tiramisu-making-experience-in-rome\u002F","id":141993,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Flo24vs8lsq5w60g94a25.jpg","name":"Fettuccine, Ravioli and Tiramisu Making Experience in Rome"},"review_content":"We had a wonderful pasta making experience with Chef Mimi. We made tiramisu as a group and then individually made both fettuccini and ravioli. Followed by an amazing shared meal with our group. Great activity for families with older kids!","review_id":18329619,"translate_content":"We had a wonderful pasta making experience with Chef Mimi. We made tiramisu as a group and then individually made both fettuccini and ravioli. Followed by an amazing shared meal with our group. Great activity for families with older kids!","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-04-24 19:06:47","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Klook User","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F87787-private-professional-photoshoot-rome\u002F","id":87787,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Frd3lgmnf2qqicszdjugw.jpg","name":"Private Professional Photoshoot in Rome"},"review_content":"Super easy booking on Klook. Phateme was punctual and made us feel comfortable during the shoot, even though we’re shy and awkward. The photos looked natural, and we got the edited images the next day. Highly recommended!","review_id":17429855,"translate_content":"Super easy booking on Klook. Phateme was punctual and made us feel comfortable during the shoot, even though we’re shy and awkward. The photos looked natural, and we got the edited images the next day. Highly recommended!","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-01-04 14:48:12","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Toni *******","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F111690-pasta-and-tiramisu-cooking-experience-in-rome-with-expert-chef\u002F","id":111690,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fapd49hbg8dsgacq931gy.jpg","name":"2-in-1: Rome Pasta and Tiramisu Cooking Class near the Colosseum"},"review_content":"Irma and Johana were great hosts and were very attentive to everyone. They made sure that everyone felt included and were great with the kids. I am vegan and allowed me to still particiapte and take the tirimisu home for my son to eat later because I could not eat it. I would recommend this class to people of all ages. ","review_id":18323916,"translate_content":"Irma and Johana were great hosts and were very attentive to everyone. They made sure that everyone felt included and were great with the kids. I am vegan and allowed me to still particiapte and take the tirimisu home for my son to eat later because I could not eat it. I would recommend this class to people of all ages. ","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-04-23 17:08:20","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Klook User","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F126577-pasta-making-class-cook-dine-and-drink-with-a-local-chef-in-rome\u002F","id":126577,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fdfqfqhddlakmqb9k6quj.jpg","name":"Pasta-Making Class with Local Chef in Rome"},"review_content":"We had a wonderful time learning how to make pasta!   The two Alessandros did an amazing job with their knowledge of the history of pasta making as well as their expertise.  .   They were very personable and shared their experiences growing up making pasta.  They truly made my first time in Rome a very memorrable one!  ","review_id":18299610,"translate_content":"We had a wonderful time learning how to make pasta!   The two Alessandros did an amazing job with their knowledge of the history of pasta making as well as their expertise.  .   They were very personable and shared their experiences growing up making pasta.  They truly made my first time in Rome a very memorrable one!  ","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-04-19 19:57:32","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Klook User","user_rating":"5.0"}},{"product_info":{"deeplink":"activity\u002F104414-spiritz-spaghetti-cooking-class-rome\u002F","id":104414,"image":"https:\u002F\u002Fres.klook.com\u002Fimage\u002Fupload\u002Factivities\u002Fmafbpy6cxvaixwugdgh1.jpg","name":"Rome Tipsy Cooking Class: Make Pasta & Taste 3 Spritz Cocktails "},"review_content":"Our group of 7 had the best time at our class and it was one of the highlights of our time in Italy. The sprits flowed generously, the instructions throughout the class were easy to follow (even after a few sprits refills).. not to mention our host was there to help.. and was an absolute vibe! We laughed a lot, learned real techniques we’ll actually use again, left full and ‘slightly’ buzzed. If you’re looking for a cooking class that’s more fun than formal, but still extremely useful.. this is 100% the one to book!","review_id":17613606,"translate_content":"Our group of 7 had the best time at our class and it was one of the highlights of our time in Italy. The sprits flowed generously, the instructions throughout the class were easy to follow (even after a few sprits refills).. not to mention our host was there to help.. and was an absolute vibe! We laughed a lot, learned real techniques we’ll actually use again, left full and ‘slightly’ buzzed. If you’re looking for a cooking class that’s more fun than formal, but still extremely useful.. this is 100% the one to book!","user_info":{"rating_desc":"Fantastic","rating_time":"2026-01-26 14:31:33","user_avatar":"","user_name":"Kaitlyn ********","user_rating":"5.0"}}]}}}}},{"meta":{"type":"any","placeholder":"","track":{"iht_spm":"CityTravelTips","iht_extra_info":null},"name":"DestinationTips"},"data":null,"body":{"content":{"handler":"marketing","data_type":"DestinationTips","load_type":"sync","src":"","track":null,"data":{"title":"Quick facts about Rome","city_id":92,"best_time_to_vist_items":[{"month_i18n":"SEP","festival_name":"Sagra dell'Uva"}],"session_weather":[{"month_from_i18n":"DEC","month_to_i18n":"FEB","high":12,"low":2,"desc":""},{"month_from_i18n":"MAR","month_to_i18n":"MAY","high":21,"low":8,"desc":""},{"month_from_i18n":"JUN","month_to_i18n":"AUG","high":31,"low":18,"desc":""},{"month_from_i18n":"SEP","month_to_i18n":"NOV","high":24,"low":9,"desc":""}],"session_weather_temperature":"C","exchang_rate":[{"to_currency":"EUR","to_currency_i18n":"Euro","from_currency":"USD","exchange_rate":"1USD = 0.88EUR"}],"current_time_zone":"+01:00","official_language_list":[{"code":"it","language":"it_IT","content":"Italian"}],"best_days_to_travel":"3","flight_duration":{"flight_time":"12","origin_city_name":"Los Angeles"},"total":0,"electric_plugs":{"type":"","img_url":""},"currency_i18ns":[{"currency":"EUR","currency_i18n":"Euro","symbol":"€","language":"en_US"}],"latlng":"41.902783,12.496365"}}}},{"meta":{"type":"any","placeholder":"","track":{"iht_spm":"WhatToKnowBeforeVisiting","iht_extra_info":null},"name":"DestinationRichContent"},"data":null,"body":{"content":{"handler":"marketing","data_type":"DestinationRichContent","load_type":"sync","src":"","track":null,"data":{"title":"What to know before visiting Rome","content":"### Top Attractions in Rome\n\n#### Colosseum and Roman Forum\n\nWhen you visit Rome, start with the [Colosseum](https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200500-colosseum\u002F) and Roman Forum, where you can walk through ancient ruins and imagine life during the Roman Empire. A guided tour helps you skip the long lines and learn about the city’s epic history.\n\n#### Vatican City and St. Peter’s Basilica\n\nHead to Vatican City, one of the most famous religious sites in Rome, Italy. Visit [St. Peter’s Basilica](https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200804-st-peters-basilica\u002F) and the Vatican Museums to see breathtaking art, including the Sistine Chapel painted by Michelangelo.\n\n#### Trevi Fountain\n\nThe [Trevi Fountain](https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50109531-trevi-fountain\u002F) is one of Rome’s most famous landmarks and a must-see for first-time visitors. Toss a coin over your left shoulder to make a wish and enjoy the sound of rushing water in this romantic spot.\n\n#### Piazza Navona\n\nIn Rome’s city center, [Piazza Navona](https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200308-piazza-navona\u002F) is a lively square filled with street artists, fountains, and cafes. You can people-watch, grab some Italian food, or admire the beautiful sculptures by Pietro Bernini.\n\n#### Spanish Steps and Piazza di Spagna\n\nClimb the Spanish Steps in Rome to see one of the city’s most iconic landmarks. At the base lies Piazza di Spagna, a stylish area surrounded by designer shops and elegant buildings like the Spanish Embassy.\n\n### Tips before visiting Rome\n\n#### 1. Get a Europe eSIM\n\nBefore visiting Rome, buy a [Europe eSIM](https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Factivity\u002F109398-europe-esim-high-speed-internet-qr-code-in-the-voucher\u002F) so you can easily access maps, book guided tours, and stay connected without hunting for Wi-Fi. It’s the most convenient option for travelers exploring multiple European cities.\n\n#### 2. Dress Modestly at Religious Sites\n\nWhen visiting Vatican City or St. Peter’s Basilica, make sure your shoulders and knees are covered. Modest clothing is required to enter many churches and religious landmarks in Rome, Italy.\n\n#### 3. Book Tickets in Advance\n\nPopular tourist attractions like the Colosseum, Roman Forum, and Vatican Museums often have long lines, especially during high season. Book your tickets early to secure your preferred time slot.\n\n#### 4. Wear Comfortable Shoes\n\nRome is very walkable, but its cobblestone streets can be uneven. Wear sturdy, comfortable shoes to explore the city center and famous landmarks without getting sore feet.\n\n#### 5. Eat Like a Local\n\nSkip touristy restaurants near major Rome landmarks and head to local trattorias for authentic Italian food. Try fresh pasta, pizza, and gelato in neighborhoods like Trastevere or Campo de Fiori.\n"}}}},{"meta":{"type":"any","placeholder":"","track":{"iht_spm":"FaqAnswer_LIST","iht_extra_info":null},"name":"DestinationFaq"},"data":null,"body":{"content":{"handler":"marketing","data_type":"DestinationFaq","load_type":"sync","src":"","track":null,"data":{"title":"FAQs about Rome","faq_list":[{"answer":"November is the rainiest month in Rome, with about 4–5 inches of rainfall. It’s a good time to visit indoor sites like the Vatican Museums or Capitoline Museums while enjoying the cozy side of the Eternal City.\n","question":"What is the rainiest month in Rome?\n"},{"answer":"Yes! Many tourist attractions in Rome are within walking distance, like the Piazza Navona, Trevi Fountain, and Campo de Fiori. Wear comfy shoes for the cobblestone streets and enjoy the lively squares along the way.\n","question":"Is Rome walkable?\n"},{"answer":"Rome can be pricey, but you can manage costs by eating at local trattorias and using public transport. Budget travelers spend around €55–€120 daily, while luxury stays in this Italian city can cost much more during high season.\n","question":"Is Rome very expensive?\n"},{"answer":"Rome is known for its ancient history, Roman monuments, and iconic landmarks like the Colosseum, Trevi Fountain, and Vatican City. The city is also famous for its amazing Italian food like pasta and amazing fountains and churches from Roman times.\n","question":"What is Rome in Italy known for?\n"},{"answer":"The best time to visit Rome, Italy, is April, May, September, or October. These months offer pleasant weather and fewer tourists at popular attractions in Rome, Italy, like the Colosseum and Roman Forum.\n","question":"What is the best month to travel to Rome?\n"},{"answer":"For your first visit, stay in the Historic Center (Centro Storico) for easy access to top Rome landmarks. Trastevere offers a charming neighborhood feel, while Piazza di Spagna and Prati are great for style and safety near Vatican City. Budget travelers can stay near Termini Station, though it’s busier at night.\n","question":"Where to stay in Rome?\n"}]}}}},{"meta":{"type":"any","placeholder":"","track":{"iht_spm":"Recommended","iht_extra_info":null},"name":"Recommended"},"data":null,"body":{"content":{"handler":"platform","data_type":"InternalLinking","load_type":"sync","src":"","track":null,"data":{"title":"Explore more on Klook","seo_static_link":[{"search_type":"","search_key":"","heading":"Top attractions in Rome","heading_ref":"city_popular_poi","linking":[{"key_word":"Colosseum","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200500-colosseum\u002F"},{"key_word":"Pantheon","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50174656-pantheon\u002F"},{"key_word":"Trevi Fountain","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50109531-trevi-fountain\u002F"},{"key_word":"Borghese Gallery","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50071724-borghese-gallery\u002F"},{"key_word":"Palatine Hill","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50336550-palatine-hill\u002F"},{"key_word":"Arch of Constantine","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50128577-arch-of-constantine\u002F"},{"key_word":"Catacombe di San Callisto","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp60280241-catacombe-di-san-callisto\u002F"},{"key_word":"Piazza Navona","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200308-piazza-navona\u002F"},{"key_word":"Trastevere","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50357890-trastevere\u002F"},{"key_word":"Spanish Steps","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp50200513-spanish-steps\u002F"},{"key_word":"Domus Aurea","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp60592392-domus-aurea\u002F"},{"key_word":"Ostia Antica","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fp60610093-ostia-antica\u002F"}]},{"search_type":"","search_key":"","heading":"Everything you need for your Rome visit","heading_ref":"city_popular_vertical","linking":[{"key_word":"Rome Hotels","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fc92-rome\u002F3-hotel\u002F"},{"key_word":"Rome Car rentals","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fcar-rentals\u002Fcity\u002F92-rome-car-rentals\u002F"},{"key_word":"Rome Private airport transfers","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fairport-transfers\u002Fservice\u002Ffco-leonardo-da-vinci%E2%80%93fiumicino-airport\u002F"},{"key_word":"Rome Tours","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.klook.com\u002Fen-US\u002Fdestination\u002Fc92-rome\u002F1001-tours\u002F"},{"key_wor